2010-05-17  Felix Palmen <felix@palmen-it.de>

First release ever: 0.0.1 (alpha)
This release is just for testing, does nothing but show falling rocks.

* stoneage.c (handleKeyboardEvent): Make CTRL+N restart the randomly
level, so falling code and memory management issues with creating and
destroying objects and events can be tested and debugged.

* README: Initial content, describes versioning scheme and some basic
policies

* INSTALL: Initial content, describes custom ./configure-options

